  <h3 id="lecture-timings">Lecture timings</h3>
  <p>Mondays and Tuesday: 9:00AM to 10:30AM (Online classes till the end of January 2022)</p>

  <h3 id="lab-timings">Lab timings</h3>
  <p>Labs start from February 2022.</p>

  <p>Tue: 2:00PM - 5:00PM, Sat: 9:00AM - 12:00PM</p>

  <h3 id="course-modules">Course Modules</h3>
  <h4 id="module-01-introduction-to-measurement">Module 01: Introduction to measurement</h4>
  <p><sub>Measurement; Measuring instrument; Transducer &amp; sensors; Generalized static characteristics of sensors; Generalized dynamic characteristics; Error analysis; Sampling</sub></p>

  <ul>
    <li>Lecture Slides: [<a href="https://github.com/siva82kb/teaching/raw/master/transducers_and_instrumentation/lectures/module01-01.pdf">01</a>] [<a href="https://github.com/siva82kb/teaching/raw/master/transducers_and_instrumentation/lectures/module01-02.pdf">02</a>] | 
Assignment</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 id="module-02-analog-signal-processing">Module 02: Analog Signal Processing</h4>
  <p><sub>Operational amplifier; Linear circuits with op-amps; First order and second order filters. System identification.</sub></p>

  <ul>
    <li>Lecture Slides | 
Assignment</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 id="module-03-measuring-movements-linear-and-rotational">Module 03: Measuring movements: linear and rotational</h4>
  <p><sub>Resistive; Inductive; Capacitive; Digital sensors; Camera based tracking; Accelerometer; Gyroscope.</sub></p>

  <ul>
    <li>Lecture Slides |
Assignment</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 id="module-04-measuring-effort-force-and-torque">Module 04: Measuring effort: Force and Torque</h4>
  <p><sub>Strain gauge; Piezoelectric sensors.</sub></p>

  <ul>
    <li>Lecture Slides | 
Assignment</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 id="module-05-measuring-pressure-flow-volume">Module 05: Measuring pressure, flow, volume.</h4>
